This paper discusses the use of AI algorithms and their potential for bias and unfairness, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also touches on the ethical and societal implications of algorithmic decision-making, which could be classified under the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of datasets in this field, which could be classified under the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY).
